* Turkmenistan has an embassy in Minsk.
|--valign=&quot;top&quot;
|{{flag|Ukraine}}||&lt;!--Date Started--&gt;||See [[Belarus–Ukraine relations]]

* The two countries share 891&amp;nbsp;km of border.
* Belarus has an embassy in [[Kiev]] and an honorary consulate in [[Lviv]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.belembassy.org.ua/  Belarussian embassy in Kiev (in Russian only)]&lt;/ref&gt;
* Ukraine has an embassy in Minsk and a general consulate in [[Brest, Belarus|Brest]].&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.belarus.mfa.gov.ua/  Ukrainian embassy in Minsk (in Russian and Ukrainian only)]&lt;/ref&gt;
* Both countries are full members of the [[Baku Initiative]], [[Common Economic Space]], [[Central European Initiative]] and [[Commonwealth of Independent States]].
|--valign=&quot;top&quot;
|{{flag|United Kingdom}}||&lt;!--Date Started--&gt;1991
|
* In 1994, Belarus opened its embassy in London.&lt;ref&gt;[http://uk.belembassy.org/  Belarussian embassy in London]&lt;/ref&gt;
* In 1995, the British embassy in Minsk was opened.&lt;ref&gt;[http://ukinbelarus.fco.gov.uk/  British embassy in Minsk]&lt;/ref&gt;
* [http://www.fco.gov.uk/en/about-the-fco/country-profiles/europe/belarus  British Foreign and Commonwealth Office about relations with Belarus]
|--valign=&quot;top&quot;
|{{flag|United States}}||&lt;!--Date Started--&gt;1991||See [[Belarus – United States relations]]

[[Interstate relations]] between the United States and Belarus began in 1991 upon the dissolution of the Soviet Union, of which Belarus had been a part. However, the relations have turned sour due to accusations by the United States that Belarus has been undemocratic. Belarus, in turn, has accused the United States of interfering in its internal affairs.
|--valign=&quot;top&quot;
|{{flag|Uzbekistan}}||&lt;!--Date Started--&gt;1992
